    "In the heart of the Basque Country, Ainhoa is considered one of the most beautiful villages in France. Its typical Basque houses are notably on the way to Compostela as well as the GR 10.",
    "Beautiful views on either side. Super flowy for an un-built trail. Be careful of the weather though, it can get quite dangerously windy.",
    "Right on the France-Spain border is this marvelous site at 710 meters above sea level in the heart of the Pyrenees. A few meters away is a center with archaeological and megalithic remains. An ideal place to take a break and enjoy the beautiful landscape that surrounds it."
